# Architecture

## Monorepo layout

- app/
  - pages/, components/ — Nuxt UI
  - stores/ — Pinia stores (authStore, listStore)
  - composables/ — Fetch and UI helpers (useAPI, useAppFetch, useSnapshotMode, etc.)
  - server/ — API, services, queues, cron, env
    - api/ — REST handlers (H3). File name encodes HTTP method: <name>.<method>.ts
    - clients/ — prismaClient, redisClient, postmarkClient, natsClient, queuesClient, openaiClient
    - lib/ — server helpers (auth, access checks, errors, pagination, Plaid utils, crypto helpers)
    - services/ — domain services (PlaidSyncService, TransactionMatchingService, Forecast/*, Reports/*, Notifications, etc.)
    - queues/ — BullMQ queue definitions (backup, plaid sync, recalc)
    - cron/ — nuxt-cron tasks (plaid, recalc, backups, bill reminders, crypto balance)
    - middleware/ — server auth/sitemap middleware
    - routes/ — non-API routes (health endpoints, sitemap, _nuxt asset route)
  - prisma/ — Prisma schema, migrations, client generation, reencrypt codegen
  - schema/ — Zod schemas for payload validation
  - lib/ — shared app-side libs (bankers rounding, sorting, utils, notifications, timezoneOptions, etc.)
  - plugins/ — client/server plugins (API init, snapshot menu, security headers, graceful)
  - tests/ — E2E Playwright (public + authed), nuxt smoke, server middleware, helpers
  - vitest.* — test configs and setup
- microservice/
  - server.ts — H3 listener bootstrapping
  - routes/ — migrate.get.ts/.post.ts, test.get.ts
  - prisma/ — independent Prisma schema, reencrypt/, migrations, seed-country.sql
  - clients/ — prismaClient, redisClient
  - lib/ — bull setup, normalizePrismaDmmf
  - scripts/ — k8s-rotate-db-key.sh (used by CronJob image target)

## Data flow

- UI (pages/components) uses composables (useAPI/useAppFetch) and Pinia to call /api/*
- API handlers (app/server/api/*) validate input (schema/zod), perform access checks (server/lib/accountAccess, requireAdmin), orchestrate services, and use prismaClient for DB access
- Long-running or asynchronous work is enqueued via BullMQ queues (server/queues/*) and processed in-process
- Periodic work is triggered by nuxt-cron via app/server/cron/*
- Forecast engine modules (server/services/forecast/*) read/write via a ModernCacheService and persistence layer; they have dedicated tests and a TS test-runner
- Plaid and Alchemy integrations use dedicated services and clients; crypto balances and plaid balance sync have cron/queues
- Microservice exposes migrate routes to support field-encryption re-encrypt/rotate workflows and is used by a staging CronJob in Kubernetes

## Persistence and schema governance

- MySQL 8 is the database; Prisma schema: app/prisma/schema.prisma
- Decimal(19,2) for monetary values; Decimal(36,18) for some token balances
- Field-level encryption via prisma-field-encryption; generated reencrypt/ migrators exist for User, AccountRegister, RegisterEntry, Reoccurrence, etc.
- Microservice has a pared-down schema focused on migration/key rotation use cases
- Scripts: scripts/check-prisma-schema-governance.mjs to enforce governance

## Environment and configuration

- Validation via app/server/envSchema.ts consumed by app/server/env.ts
- Sensitive runtime values from Kubernetes Secrets in prod/staging (see .deploy/*.yaml). Locally, use .env
- Health endpoints:
  - app/server/routes/health/live.get.ts
  - app/server/routes/health/ready.get.ts

## Background processing

- Queues: backupQueue.ts, plaidSyncQueue.ts, plaidSyncBalanceQueue.ts, recalculateQueue.ts
- Cron: backup.daily.ts, plaid.daily.ts, plaid-balance.hourly.ts, recalculate.hourly.ts, bill-reminders.hourly.ts, crypto-balance.hourly.ts

## Deployment model

- CI builds two images (app and microservice) with Docker Buildx; pushed to GCR
- Kubernetes manifests are rendered via envsubst from .deploy/dineros.template.yaml and applied via a composite GitHub Action
- Staging also applies a key-rotation CronJob (runner-keyrotate image target) that patches Secrets and triggers microservice migration
